com.parse4cn1

Interface Parse.IPersistable

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    ParseFile, ParseInstallation, ParseObject, ParseRole, ParseUser
    Enclosing class:
    Parse

    public static interface Parse.IPersistable
    An interface for a persistable entity.

    • Method Summary

      All Methods Instance Methods Abstract Methods 
      Modifier and Type Method and Description
      boolean isDataAvailable()
      Checks whether this persistable object has any data.
      boolean isDirty()
      An object is dirty if a change has been made to it that requires it to be persisted.
      void save()
      Saves the object.
      void setDirty(boolean dirty)
      Sets the dirty flag.

    • Method Detail

      • isDirty

        boolean isDirty()
        An object is dirty if a change has been made to it that requires it to be persisted.
        Returns:
        true if the object is dirty; otherwise false.

      • setDirty

        void setDirty(boolean dirty)
        Sets the dirty flag.
        Parameters:
        dirty - true if the object should be marked as dirty; otherwise false.

      • isDataAvailable

        boolean isDataAvailable()
        Checks whether this persistable object has any data. This data may (isDirty() = true) or may not (isDirty() = false) need to be persisted.
        Returns:
        true if this object has data.

      • save

        void save()
   throws ParseException
        Saves the object. Calling this method on an object that is not dirty should have no side effects.
        Throws:
        ParseException - if anything goes wrong during the save operation.
